The great opportunity for astronomers is now to catch glimpses of an alien solar system from close range. Apparently, the Come is similar to those of our own system, as the Astrophysical Institute of the Canary Islands reports. According to the International Astronomical Union (IAC), the comet is clearly of interstellar origin and is currently moving on a so-called hyperbolic orbit that takes it out of our system.
